  "content": "# state type names use XState not XGlobalState\n\nWhen defining a global state schema via `SET_STATE_SCHEMA` with `scope: \"global\"`, the top-level type must be named `<DocumentModelName>State`, not `<DocumentModelName>GlobalState`.\n\n```graphql\n// \u2705 CORRECT\ntype TodoListState {\n    todos: [Todo!]!\n}\n\n// \u274c WRONG \u2014 causes TypeScript compilation errors\ntype TodoListGlobalState {\n    todos: [Todo!]!\n}\n```\n\nFor local state (if needed), use `<DocumentModelName>LocalState`.\n\nThe code generator hard-codes this expectation. Using the wrong suffix means generated types won't match, and TypeScript will report missing type definitions.\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[schema design]]\n- [[gotchas]]",
